summary:
Multilingual master-qualified professional with more than 6 years of experience in project execution with a background in international business and project management. Fascinated by the circular economy, sustainability, stakeholder management, team dynamics, and data. Direct involvement in projects related to urban research, sustainable development, circular IT solutions, and carbon reduction and reporting. 

PRINCE2 Agile certified (foundation and practitioner). In addition, passionate about finding solutions to contemporary challenges by building a “new normal” way of working and living by rethinking our current system and using advanced technology. I am currently dedicated to developing sustainable solutions, reducing the environmental impact and decarbonisation of the IT sector. The new topic of interest is CSRD reporting.

Accessors were taking into consideration quality and feasibility of reports as well as our end pitch to the customer. This half a year project consisted of Business ethics paper, Economic and cultural quick-scan of the region, Trade and Finance Paper, Marketing and Sales presentation.

The International Business Challenge is first and foremost a competition between teams of students.
The competition element is essential as this is a highly realistic setting for the business environment.
Students should compete in teams for the award of the best business case for a real-life international company.
Secondly, this module prepares them for the exchange abroad in the region of your specialization. It
integrates the theory and skills from research, economics, management and organization, finance and
accounting, trade and logistics, culture, and marketing and sales into one real-life business case for the
business research project. The student will need to plan, organize, develop, and execute deliverables for a real
company. The business case focusses on a company that is active in one or more of the following
regions: Asia, South America, North America, Africa or Europe. You will work in teams of approximately.
